YouTube Audience Analysis: Weekly Patterns and Age Group Differences

Introduction

Our dataset contains 42 viewing records collected between April 07 and April 13. The analysis focuses on two key metrics: Weekly Patterns and Age Group Differences

Understanding Viewer Engagement Patterns

plot1

  • Lowest engagement happens on Wed with 23.02 total watch hours

  • Peak viewership occurs on Thu with 41.5 total watch hours

Age Group Viewing Behavior

plot2

plot3

Combined Viewing Pattern Analysis

Key insights from 13 analyzed categories:

  • Peak weekly engagement: Fri
    (92.7 seconds average)

  • Highest age group duration: 25-34
    (86.5 seconds per view)

  • Lowest age group duration: 55-64
    (61.6 seconds per view)
